fields.customfield_14135:
Allow the Printscan fingerprint card processing team to automatically generate and print shipping labels for multiple carriers (USPS, Fedex) to fulfill fingerprint cards orders. 

Implementing this service will greatly speed the fulfillment time for fingerprint card shipment, reduces manual touch on each order, and reduces reliance on external vendor shipment support (Kings Park Shipping and Printing Center).
fields.customfield_14136: Printscan needs an automated solution for generating shipping labels and inserting the newly-generated tracking numbers into the Printscan HD Lite "scheduling" tool in order to provide consistent and effective service to clients ordering fingerprint cards.
fields.customfield_14127: Using API integration with Printscan HD Lite tool, Shipstation will consume incoming card printing requests and generate a label/tracking number. The tracking number will be automatically attached to the applicant's order, triggering a notification that their cards are about to ship. The labels will be queued to print simultaneously with the fingerprint cards. Shipstation will have access to applicant First/Last Name, Address.
